    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect PMI index calculation in gNB scheduler\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_pm_index()` function in `gNB_scheduler_primitives.c` was calculating antenna ports incorrectly, leading to wrong PMI selection and potential undefined behavior. This fix corrects the antenna port calculation and improves error handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: \n  - Fixed antenna ports calculation from `(N1*N2)<<1` to `N1*N2*xp_pdsch_antenna_ports`\n  - Improved condition check for XP antenna configurations\n  - Added proper return paths for all cases including single antenna port\n  - Replaced fatal assertion with graceful error handling for unsupported configurations\n  - Added warning logging for unsupported antenna port configurations\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue manifests when running OAI gNB with non-standard antenna port configurations where XP=1 but N1>1 or N2>1. Users may observe incorrect PMI selection leading to suboptimal MIMO performance or scheduler failures. In some cases, the function could return undefined values causing unpredictable behavior in the PDSCH scheduler.\n\nConfiguration files using non-default `pdsch_AntennaPorts_N1`, `pdsch_AntennaPorts_N2`, or `pdsch_AntennaPorts_XP` values are particularly affected.\n"
}